Wash and dry all produce. Bring a medium #pot of salted water to a boil. Thinly slice @scallions{2}, keeping greens and whites separate. Slice @cucumber{1} into thin rounds. Halve @lemon{1}.

Once water is boiling, add @gemelli pasta{6%ounce} to #pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Carefully scoop out and reserve ½ cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tablespoon} in a large #pan over medium-high heat. Season @chicken breasts{24%ounce} all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add to pan and cook until no longer pink in center, ~{5-6%minutes} per side.

After draining gemelli, heat a large drizzle of oil in #pot used to cook it over medium heat. Add scallion whites and cook, tossing, until softened, about ~{1%minute}. Add gemelli, @cheddar cheese{1%cup}, @cream cheese{2%ounce}, @butter{1%tablespoon}, and reserved pasta cooking water. Stir until a creamy sauce forms. Season generously with salt and pepper.

Once chicken is cooked through, add @BBQ sauce{4%tablespoon} to same #pan. Turn chicken to coat in sauce. In a large #bowl, toss together @mixed greens{4%ounce}, cucumber, a few squeezes of lemon, and a large drizzle of @olive oil{}. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide chicken, mac 'n' cheese, and salad between plates.

> If mac 'n' cheese has become stiff, add a splash of water and reheat briefly over low heat.

Drizzle chicken with any remaining sauce in pan. Sprinkle scallion greens over everything and serve.